# PATH: .gitignore
# PURPOSE:
# - Prevents sensitive information from being committed to version control.
# - Protects financial data, personal information, and proprietary content.

# ROLE IN ARCHITECTURE:
# - Security layer: ensures sensitive RDTI filing information is not exposed.

# NON-RESPONSIBILITIES:
# - Does NOT handle encryption or access control
# - Does NOT manage backup or archival systems

# NOTES FOR FUTURE AI:
# - Never commit files containing sensitive financial or personal information
# - Review this file regularly to ensure all sensitive file types are covered
# - Consider using git-secrets or similar tools for additional protection

# Sensitive Financial Documents
*.xlsx
*.xls
*.csv
*financial*.pdf
*invoice*.pdf
*receipt*.pdf
*cost*.pdf
*budget*.pdf

# Personal Information
*timesheet*.pdf
*timesheet*.xlsx
*employee*.pdf
*payroll*.pdf
*personal*.pdf

# Tax and Legal Documents
*tax*.pdf
*legal*.pdf
*contract*.pdf
*agreement*.pdf

# Proprietary Information
*proprietary*.pdf
*confidential*.pdf
*secret*.pdf

# Backup Files
*.bak
*.backup
*~*
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Temporary Files
*.tmp
*.temp
*.log

# Office Temporary Files
~$*.docx
~$*.xlsx
~$*.pptx

# Archive Files (may contain sensitive data)
*.zip
*.rar
*.7z
*.tar.gz

# Notes:
# - If you need to track certain file types, create a separate secure repository
# - Consider using encrypted storage for sensitive documents
# - Use environment variables or secure vaults for any credentials
.env.local
